def median(x):
    N = len(x)
    x.sort()
    if N % 2 == 0: # if N is even
        m1 = N/2
        m2 = (N/2) + 1
        # convert to integer, match position
        m1 = int(m1) - 1
        m2 = int(m2) - 1
        median = (x[m1] + x[m2])/2
    else:
        m = (N+1)/2
        # convert to integer, match position
        m = int(m) - 1
        median = x[m]
    return median

def quantile(x, p):
    """returns the pth-percentile value in x"""
    p_index = int(p * len(x))
    return sorted(x)[p_index]

def mode(x):
    counts = Counter(x)
    max_count = max(counts.values())
    return [x_i for x_i, count in counts.iteritems() if count == max_count]

def variance(x):
    return sum([(xi - mean(x))**2 for xi in x])/float(len(x))
def svariance(x):
    return sum([(xi - mean(x))**2 for xi in x])/float(len(x)-1)

def barplot(data,offset):  
    n = len(data)
    X = range(n)
    Y = data
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    plt.bar(X, Y, facecolor='#9999ff', edgecolor='black')
    for a,b in zip(X, Y):
        plt.text(a + 0.4, b + 0.05, '%i' % b, ha='center', va='bottom')
    plt.xlim(-.5, n)
    plt.ylim(0, max(data) + offset)
    plt.xticks(X)

def barplot(labels,data,offset):
    n = len(labels)
    X = range(n)
    Y = data
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    plt.bar(X, Y, facecolor='#9999ff', edgecolor='black')
    for a,b in zip(X, Y):
        plt.text(a + 0.4, b + 0.05, '%i' % b, ha='center', va='bottom')
    plt.xlim(-.5, n)
    plt.xticks(X,labels,rotation='vertical',ha='left')
    plt.ylim(0, max(data) + offset)

def histogram(data,xname,yname,bins,xticks=True):   #offset,
    data_counts = Counter(data)
    n = max(data_counts.keys())
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    plt.hist(data, bins=bins, facecolor='#9999ff', edgecolor='black')
    stitl="Histogram of %s Counts" %xname     
    plt.title(stitl)
    if xticks:
        plt.xticks(data,rotation='vertical',ha='left')   
    xtitl="# of %s" %xname
    ytitl="# of %s" %yname
    plt.xlabel(xtitl)
    plt.ylabel(ytitl)
